'''''Mycobacterium avium'' complex (MAC)''' is a group of genetically related [[bacteria]] belonging to the genus ''[[Mycobacterium]]''. It includes ''[[Mycobacterium avium]]'' and ''[[Mycobacterium intracellulare]]''.<ref name="WHITE2004">{{cite book|author=LOIS WHITE|title=FOUNDATIONS OF NURSING|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=xSFunA58p8gC&pg=PA1298|accessdate=5 November 2010|date=7 July 2004|publisher=Cengage Learning|isbn=978-1-4018-2692-5|pages=1298–}}</ref><ref name="urlDisease Listing, Mycobacterium avium Complex, Tech Info | CDC Bacterial, Mycotic Diseases">{{cite web |url=http://www.cdc.gov/ncidod/dbmd/diseaseinfo/mycobacteriumavium_t.htm |title=Disease Listing, Mycobacterium avium Complex, Tech Info &#124; CDC Bacterial, Mycotic Diseases |format= |work= |accessdate=2010-11-04}}</ref>

Some sources also include [[Mycobacterium avium subspecies paratuberculosis|''Mycobacterium avium'' subspecies ''paratuberculosis'']] ('''MAP''').<ref name="IrvingRampton2006">{{cite book|author1=Peter Irving|author2=David Rampton|author3=Fergus Shanahan|title=Clinical dilemmas in inflammatory bowel disease|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=mc5xDyUtNAQC&pg=PA36|accessdate=5 November 2010|date=21 July 2006|publisher=Wiley-Blackwell|isbn=978-1-4051-3377-7|pages=36–}}</ref>

